Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 328/88 of 2 February 1988 instituting a Community programme to assist the conversion of steel areas (Resider programme) (1), and in particular Article 3 and 4 thereof,
Whereas Article 3 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 328/88 stipulates that the Community programme shall apply to areas which satisfy the criteria specified in Article 3 (1) and the thresholds laid down by Article 4 (1);
Whereas the Member State concerned must submit an application for approval of the areas to which the Community programme is to apply; whereas Spain has submitted such an application to the Commission in respect of the Autonomous Community of Asturias and areas of the Basque Country;
Whereas these areas satisfy the abovementioned criteria,
